  <!-- ================= NAMING & USAGE RULES ================= -->
  <section class="section" id="sec-rules" data-section="rules">
    <h2 class="sec-title">Naming conventions &amp; usage rules</h2>
    <div class="rules-grid">
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Token naming</h3>
        <p>Primitives are <code>--color-&lt;family&gt;-&lt;step&gt;</code> / <code>--text-&lt;size&gt;</code>. Semantic tokens are <code>--color-&lt;role&gt;</code> (surface / text / border / action / state / field).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Binding direction</h3>
        <p>Components bind to <b>semantic</b>; semantic binds to <b>primitive</b>. Never bind a component to a raw hex or primitive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>8px grid</h3>
        <p>Every gap / padding / margin / box size is a multiple of 8px (4px worst case). No off-grid 6 / 10 / 14 / 18.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Solid hex only</h3>
        <p>Every fill / stroke / border is a solid hex. Translucency is allowed only for <code>box-shadow</code>, frosted <code>backdrop-filter</code>, and the <code>opacity</code> property in motion.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>One font</h3>
        <p>Outfit only, site-wide — no second family. Form controls force-inherit it. Every text element renders at line-height 1.5.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Icon sizes</h3>
        <p>Icons are real <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code>s — never text glyphs — sized <b>16 / 20 / 24 / 32px</b> only, chosen from context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Heading alignment</h3>
        <p>The hero H1, every <code>.sec-title</code> and every <code>.sub-title</code> (with their leads) are <b>left-aligned</b> — never centred, no <code>max-width</code> cap on the lead. The only centred text is the promotional bands (<code>.cta-box</code> and dark CTA / access bands). Reference: <code>products/equity.astro</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rule">
        <h3>Mobile tap targets</h3>
        <p>Every tappable control presents a <b>≥44px</b> touch area on mobile — the site standard is <b>48px</b> (on the 8px grid, matching <code>.hf-field</code> and <code>.to-top</code>). <b>Pad out the hit area</b>, never enlarge the icon: the glyph stays on its 16/20/24/32 scale while the container / <code>min-width</code> / <code>min-height</code> grows to 48px. See footer <code>.socials a</code> and <code>.nav-toggle</code>. This governs tap area, not font size — micro-labels (the <code>.hf-field</code> floating label ~10px) are a sanctioned exception.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
